Haskell LLSD & LLIDL library
----------------------------
    v1 - 2010-06-07 - Zero Linden (Mark Lentczner)


ABOUT
=====
LLSD is defined in draft-hamrick-vwrap-type-system-00. It is a structured data
system used for interchange. See the draft for more details:

    http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-hamrick-vwrap-type-system-00

This implementation handles XML and Binary serialization, and a full LLIDL
parser and checker.

To see the interface, consult:
    Network/Format/LLSD.hs
    Network/Format/LLSD/LLIDL.hs
    

BUILDING
========
Build with cabal:

    cabal configure -ftest
    cabal build

EXECUTABLES
===========
There are two executables included (assuming you use -ftest):

    llsdutil -- converts between serializations
    testllsd -- unit tests and simple data generator / consumer for timing tests

